# API integration pre-push gate (umbraculum-class monorepos)

## Two-tier pre-push (hard)

| Tier | Tool | Catches | Does **not** catch |
|------|------|---------|---------------------|
| **1 — Static analysis** | `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity` (jobs from `.umbraculum/ci-parity.json`) | TS errors in tests (`tsc --noEmit`), lint, docs | Vitest runtime, Redis/BullMQ teardown, DB integration |
| **2 — API integration** | **`api-integration-tests-pre-push`** skill | GHA `api` workflow failures (`npm test`, unhandled vitest rejections with `REDIS_URL`) | Playwright e2e, deploy, DNS |

When editing **`services/api/**`**, API test files, **`buildApp()`** boot paths, or shared packages in `.github/workflows/api.yml` path filters: run **both tiers** before push.

## Rule (hard)

1. **Do not treat `docker compose exec api npm run typecheck` or a green dev UI as sufficient** for API changes.
2. **Do not treat ci-parity alone as sufficient** for API changes — it does not execute `services/api` vitest with Redis.
3. **Treat vitest "Tests passed" + "Unhandled Errors" / `Errors: 1` as FAIL** — CI exits non-zero the same way.
4. Procedure: skill **`api-integration-tests-pre-push`** (this plugin). Static analysis: skill **`ci-parity-local-reproduction`** + rule **`72-ci-parity-local-vs-ci-divergence`**.

## Agent anti-patterns

| Anti-pattern | Why it fails |
|---|---|
| Push after only manual browser check | Misses test-file TS errors and vitest teardown |
| `vitest run` without Redis when CI sets `REDIS_URL` | Misses BullMQ/ioredis lifecycle bugs |
| Ignoring unhandled rejection summary | CI fails despite 542 passed tests |

## Runbook

Skill: `api-integration-tests-pre-push` in this plugin.
